An expectant lawyer, Nkiru Agbasu, has been shot dead by suspected armed robbers on the Warri/Sapele Expressway in Delta State. The Nation gathered that the incident happened on Tuesday afternoon, while she was returning from Sapele. Agbasu was said to have been the only one struck by a bullet, as the hoodlums shot at the vehicle she was riding. Chairman of the Nigerian Bar Association, Warri Branch, Chief Emmanuel O. Uti, confirmed the incident to The Nation on Wednesday. “She was on her way from Sapele,” Uti said. “It was an armed robbery and they shot at their car. She was the one the bullet hit.” Police spokesperson Onome  Onovwakpoyeya did not confirm the incident as calls to her phone rang out.